				<td colspan="2"><span>I was not talking about looting gear.  I had this happen the night before the patch, I faded three times, and still died.  Upon rezoning at bind point I still had the exact same mana I had right before dying.  That is to say, I had the same mana left, although the mana bar was a tad higher than right before death.  This is due to the loss of VoQ mostly I think.
<br />

<br />
The same thing happened last night, after the patch.  Two different zones, same net results.  Another guild bard also stated it happening to them last night.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes when there are patches scheduled I've noticed that parts of the patch are available at times before the servers are actually down.  I didn't stay at the computer while loading the night before, as I was busy nuking a snack while EQ was loading.  It is possible, as has happened before, that I got some of the patch prior to the servers being taken down, hence seeing the behavior the night before.  This stands to reason from everything I've seen, as this type of stuff has happened consistently with almost every patching that I can recall (albeit no patch message).
<br />

<br />
Polara Magami</span></td>
